{"parse":{"title":"Operation Red Card","pageid":7118025,"revid":799353928,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><i><b>Operation Red Card</b></i> is the name given to a two-month Asia-wide <a href=\"/wiki/Copyright_infringement\" title=\"Copyright infringement\">anti-piracy</a> operation that was conducted by the Motion Picture Association (MPA) (the international arm of the <a href=\"/wiki/Motion_Picture_Association_of_America\" title=\"Motion Picture Association of America\">Motion Picture Association of America</a>) which resulted in the seizure of 6.7 million pirated discs in 12 countries across the <a href=\"/wiki/Asia-Pacific\" title=\"Asia-Pacific\">Asia-Pacific</a> region. The operation took place between May to mid-July 2006, resulting in 915 arrests and the seizure of 1,483 optical disc burners.\n</p><p>There were 1,919 raids conducted in 12 countries throughout Asia.  \n</p>\n<ul><li>In <a href=\"/wiki/China\" title=\"China\">China</a>, 405 raids resulted in the seizure of over 1.96 million discs.</li>\n<li>Raids in <a href=\"/wiki/Indonesia\" title=\"Indonesia\">Indonesia</a> brought in 305 <a href=\"/wiki/Optical_disc_recording_technologies\" title=\"Optical disc recording technologies\">DVD burners</a> and 2.16 million discs.</li>\n<li>In <a href=\"/wiki/Malaysia\" title=\"Malaysia\">Malaysia</a>, there were 128 arrests and 1.18 million <a href=\"/wiki/Optical_discs\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Optical discs\">optical discs</a> seized in 455 raids.</li></ul>\n<p>The MPAA has been conducting anti-piracy sweeps on a twice a year basis, with more than 2,500 arrests and the seizure of over 23 million illegal videos so far.\n</p><p>According to the MPAA, its members\u2014which encompass all of the major film studios in Hollywood\u2014lost $1.2 billion a year in revenue due to piracy and illegal downloading.<sup class=\"reference plainlinks nourlexpansion\" id=\"ref_cite_news\"><a class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operation_Red_Card#endnote_cite_news\">[1]</a></sup>\n</p><p>The name <i>Operation Red Card</i> is a reference to the red card issued by a referee to a player ejected from a <a href=\"/wiki/Football\" title=\"Football\">football</a> game for unsportsmanlike conduct or repeated <a href=\"/wiki/Foul_(football)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Foul (football)\">fouls</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Operation_Red_Card&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation news\">Ellis, Mike (2006-07-25). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.mpaa.org/press_releases/2006_07_25.pdf\">\"ASIA-WIDE MOVIE PIRACY OPERATIONS NET RECORD 6.7 MILLION PIRATE DISCS, 915 ARRESTS\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. <i>MPA Asia-Pacific</i>. Motion Picture Association of America<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2006-07-25</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=MPA+Asia-Pacific&amp;rft.atitle=ASIA-WIDE+MOVIE+PIRACY+OPERATIONS+NET+RECORD+6.7+MILLION+PIRATE+DISCS%2C+915+ARRESTS&amp;rft.date=2006-07-25&amp;rft.aulast=Ellis&amp;rft.aufirst=Mike&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mpaa.org%2Fpress_releases%2F2006_07_25.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOperation+Red+Card\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation news\">Schwankert, Steven (2006-07-26). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20060820052301/http://www2.csoonline.com/blog_view.html?CID=23331\">\"Motion Picture Assoc. Finishes Operation Red Card with Raids\"</a>. <i>IDG News Service (Beijing Bureau)</i>. CXO Media Inc. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www2.csoonline.com/blog_view.html?CID=23331\">the original</a> on 2006-08-20<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2006-07-26</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=IDG+News+Service+%28Beijing+Bureau%29&amp;rft.atitle=Motion+Picture+Assoc.+Finishes+Operation+Red+Card+with+Raids&amp;rft.date=2006-07-26&amp;rft.aulast=Schwankert&amp;rft.aufirst=Steven&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww2.csoonline.com%2Fblog_view.html%3FCID%3D23331&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOperation+Red+Card\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1235\nCached time: 20180909132732\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.064 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.084 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 108/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 3895/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 20/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 4/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.029/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 1.42 MB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   68.087      1 -total\n 95.65%   65.125      2 Template:Cite_news\n  3.94%    2.683      1 Template:Ref\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:7118025-0!canonical and timestamp 20180909132732 and revision id 799353928\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","*":"Copyright_campaigns"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Crimes"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Copyright_infringement"},{"sortkey":"","*":"2006_in_Asia"}],"links":[{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Asia-P